# Feature Development Workflow

Apply these four phases to every new feature request. Never skip Phase 1.

## 1. Clarify & approve (no code yet)
- Dispatch parallel read-only explore agents to investigate the feature and affected code.
- Synthesize findings into clarifying questions; ask via AskQuestion.
- Iterate until the user explicitly approves scope. Do not implement until approved.

## 2. Build in parallel
- Branch off `main`: `feature/<short-name>`.
- Split into file-disjoint chunks; dispatch multiple agents in parallel.
- Each agent edits only its files and commits via explicit pathspec (never `git add -A`); retry on index.lock.
- Keep the build green (`npm run build` in `web/`) and logic checks passing.

## 3. QA in parallel
- Dispatch multiple agents for build/typecheck, lint, and functional/visual QA.
- For visual QA, start a fresh dev server (long-running ones serve stale modules).
- Fix everything found before shipping.

## 4. Ship via PR
- Push the feature branch; open a PR into `main` with `gh pr create --base main` (summary + test plan).
- Do NOT auto-merge; the user reviews and merges.

## Guardrails
- Never merge to `main` or deploy without the user's explicit go-ahead.
- Parallel agents must own disjoint files.